    "content_hash": "f45ba3eafbb2f698",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "WHY HARVEY\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate — not incrementally, but end-to-end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come.\n\nThis is a rare chance to help build a generational company at a true inflection point. With 1000+ customers in 60+ countries, strong product-market fit, and world-class investor support, we’re scaling fast and defining a new category in real time. The work is ambitious, the bar is high, and the opportunity for growth — personal, professional, and financial — is unmatched.\n\nOur team is sharp, motivated, and deeply committed to the mission. We move fast, operate with intensity, and take real ownership of the problems we tackle — from early thinking to long-term outcomes. We stay close to our customers — from leadership to engineers — and work together to solve real problems with urgency and care. If you thrive in ambiguity, push for excellence, and want to help shape the future of work alongside others who raise the bar, we invite you to build with us.\n\nAt Harvey, the future of professional services is being written today — and we’re just getting started.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nHarvey is seeking a Head of Content \u0026 Strategy to own our content engine and transform how we scale storytelling across channels. You will be responsible for building and executing a holistic content strategy that establishes Harvey as the authoritative voice in legal AI, drives awareness in key markets, and fuels the pipeline for GTM.\n\nThis role requires both editorial instinct and operational rigor. You will have a social-first mindset, understanding how to turn company moments, ideas, and product launches into high-velocity content that drives engagement and follower growth across LinkedIn, X, and Instagram.\n\nHelp shape Harvey’s story to be told across every touchpoint from long-form, thought leadership, blog, social, podcasts and video formats.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Content Strategy \u0026 Editorial Calendar: Own Harvey’s global content strategy, set the editorial calendar, and ensure alignment across GTM, Product Marketing, Partnerships, and Customer Engagement.\n\n - Content Governance \u0026 Frameworks: Define tone, voice, and editorial standards; build reusable frameworks and templates for scalable storytelling.\n\n - Thought Leadership \u0026 Category Narrative: Partner with executives and subject matter experts to develop Harvey’s POV and establish authority in the market.\n\n - Social and Customer Evangelism: Own Harvey’s organic social media strategy, editorial calendar, and manage social media agency for publishing across LinkedIn, YouTube, and emerging channels (Reddit, G2, others).\n\n - Multi-Channel Content Production: Oversee creation and distribution of content across blog, social, video, SEO, and emerging channels; ensure repurposing of high-value assets.\n\n - Analytics \u0026 SEO: Own reporting on content performance, SEO, and listening tools; translate insights into recommendations that drive reach and conversion.\n\n - Innovation \u0026 Workflow Optimization: Pilot automation and AI tools to improve production efficiency and accelerate distribution.\n\n - Leadership \u0026 Enablement: Serve as an advisor to marketing leadership; coach GTM teams on how to best leverage content in field, customer, and partner interactions. Manage the content and social marketing team of FTEs, freelancers, and agencies.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n\n - Experience in content marketing, editorial strategy, integrated marketing, and directly managed corporate social media profiles ideally with B2B SaaS or professional services exposure.\n\n - Demonstrated success building and scaling content engines that balance brand storytelling with measurable business impact.\n\n - Strong editorial judgment and ability to distill complex ideas into compelling narratives.\n\n - Experience managing multi-channel content strategies, including SEO, social, and video.\n\n - Proven ability to establish governance, processes, and scalable content frameworks.\n\n - Familiarity with AI/automation tools for marketing a plus.\n\n - Excellent communication skills, with a bias toward clarity and authority.\n\n - Comfortable operating both strategically and tactically in a fast-moving environment.\n\n\n\n\n\nCOMPENSATION\n\n$208,300 - $281,800 USD\n\n\nDEPENDING ON YOUR LOCATION, AN APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICE MAY APPLY TO YOU. YOU CAN FIND ALL OF OUR APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICES [HERE https://www.notion.so/harveyai/Harvey-Candidate-Privacy-Policies-319ac3fcdd7a803bb807d5094f249922].\n\n#LI-TM1\n\nHarvey is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made by emailing accommodations@harvey.ai",
